(In reply to Oleksandr Kryvulia from comment #7)

Looking at /usr/src/sys/dev/sound/pci/hda/pin_patch_realtek.h, it appears that this patch will also impact T430S, X230, X230T, and T431S.  Can we be sure that they all use nid=21, as=1, and seq=15?

                        }, {
                                .models = (struct pin_machine_model_t[]){
                                        PIN_SUBVENDOR(LENOVO_T430_SUBVENDOR),
                                        PIN_SUBVENDOR(LENOVO_T430S_SUBVENDOR),
                                        PIN_SUBVENDOR(LENOVO_X230_SUBVENDOR),
                                        PIN_SUBVENDOR(LENOVO_X230T_SUBVENDOR),
                                        PIN_SUBVENDOR(LENOVO_T431S_SUBVENDOR),
                                        { }
                                },
                                .pin_patches = (struct pin_patch_t[]){
                                        PIN_PATCH_DOCK_MIC_IN(25),
                                        PIN_PATCH_DOCK_HP(27),
                                        // Patch added here
                                        // PIN_PATCH_STRING(21, "as=1 seq=15"),
                                        { }
                                }
                        },

I'd have to do some research to understand what all these parameters mean.  The simple fact that they are grouped together in the .models field might imply that they use identical hardware, but I don't want to assume that given my meager knowledge of audio devices.
